      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:23:5",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " دِيَةُ الْعَبْدِ قِيمَتُهُ فَإِنْ كَانَ نَفِيساً فَأَفْضَلُ قِيمَتِهِ عَشَرَةُ آلَافِ دِرْهَمٍ وَ لَا يُجَاوَزُ بِهِ دِيَةَ الْحُرِّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from Muhammad Bin Isa, from Yunus, from Ibn Muskan, ",
          "Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> has said: ‘Wergild of the slave is his value. So if he was precious, so the highest of his value would be a thousand Dirhams, and the wergild of the free would not be exceeded by it’."
        ]
      }
